data.value: Image shape as a tuple of size 2. Determines the maximum extent of output pixel coordinates. This is useful for disks that exceed the image size. If None, the full extent of the disk is used. The  shape might result in negative coordinates and wraparound behaviour.
Pixel coordinates of disk. May be used to directly index into an array, e.g.
Generate coordinates of pixels within circle.
